Yesterday bestowed unexpected joy— an unplanned impromptu reunion with my brother @williammtwilson, four of my cousins— Lee @bubblewrath00, Maria, Sophie, Joseph, and my aunt Marlies. Sans hyperbole, it was truly born from divine timing. Many of us hadn’t seen one another in years. …36 hours ago none of us knew this would be happening. And then it happened ✨

RIP Loomiss. My angel of joy and milk thief for 12 years. You extended unconditional love to every soul that set foot into our home. Soother to Tybalt; heart healer to me… I know it was you who tap tap tap tapped on the cat door the day after your passing because Tybalt was beside me. And then that very night I felt your full weight and warmth upon my chest as I lay weeping for the vacancy beside my pillow. In that moment you alchemized a grief sourced from pain into tears born of gratitude. Joy joy joy is your paw print. Perhaps you still won’t learn to read standard American English wherever you are, but I dance in faith that the sacred sentiments of my silly words herein will caress you ad infinitum. My feelings fly for you. Rest In Play my lil baby Loomiss (c. 2008 — August 15th 2023)
good morning, God morning, gentle mourning

LAFC forever 🖤 that said, Lionel Messí is a magician. Verily. We’ve all watched him on TV, but one experiences a ripple in the space time continuum when bearing witness in-person. Time slows and defenders wobble. It’s unlike anything I’ve ever seen. He doesn’t move like a human. Inter Miami is undefeated since he joined them, and tonight they thrashed us, the defending champions, 3-1. Yet I’ve never been so calm following a loss. I witnessed the master of our generation directly assist two goals, and I also witnessed La Liga legend Jordi Alba score a banger goal. A surreal day. But a very good day. #LAFC #Messi @district9ultras (bears mentioning, however, that @rmhollingshead and @jesusdavid16 each executed a brilliant tackle against Messí)
It’s all fun and games until you become friends for life. And then it’s still fun and games.

One of the most fun projects I’ve ever been a part of, the (independent!) film @onyxthefortuitous_official is hitting big screen allllllll over LA this week! Peep me and my boi’s @monsourmichael & @kareem3k as we rain malice opposite the maestro Andrew Bowser @andrewbowserdirector who also wrote, directed, produced, and stars in the title role —also produced and starring my homie Olivia Taylor Dudley @oliviataylordudley …tickets are still avail at theonyxmovie.com …I’ll be attending the 7pm showing at Regal Sherman Oaks Galleria this Thursday 19th. The film made its world debut at this year’s Sundance Film Festival to sterling reviews. I have a special feeling about this one ✨💚
